highlights.text: Taylor Swift has the most spots on Top Albums Global. “1989 (Taylor's Version)” is the highest at #1.
“Lover” by Taylor Swift has been on Top Albums Global the longest, at 163 weeks straight.
“X2VR” by Sfera Ebbasta is the highest new entry on Top Albums Global at #8.
“Alone At Prom” by Tory Lanez is the biggest gainer on Top Albums Global, up 83 spots at #45.
